<script>
// === SETTINGS ===
const MAP_CENTER = [51.3313, -0.7414];
const MAP_ZOOM = 11;

// === EMBEDDED AREAS (paste your 12 GeoJSONs below exactly as-is) ===
const AREAS = {
  "Surrey Heath": {/* PASTE Surrey Heath geojson here */},
  "Guildford and Waverley": {/* PASTE Guildford and Waverley geojson here */},
  "Northwest Surrey": {/* PASTE Northwest Surrey geojson here */},
  "Petersfield": {/* PASTE Petersfield geojson here */},
  "Bordon": {/* PASTE Bordon geojson here */},
  "Northeast Hampshire": {/* PASTE Northeast Hampshire geojson here */},
  "Basingstoke": {/* PASTE Basingstoke geojson here */},
  "Winchester": {/* PASTE Winchester geojson here */},
  "Andover": {/* PASTE Andover geojson here */},
  "Maidenhead": {/* PASTE Maidenhead geojson here */},
  "Bracknell": {/* PASTE Bracknell geojson here */},
  "Windsor": {/* PASTE Windsor geojson here */}
};

// Stable colours
const COLOURS = {
  "Surrey Heath":"#8dd3c7",
  "Guildford and Waverley":"#ffffb3",
  "Northwest Surrey":"#bebada",
  "Petersfield":"#fb8072",
  "Bordon":"#80b1d3",
  "Northeast Hampshire":"#fdb462",
  "Basingstoke":"#b3de69",
  "Winchester":"#fccde5",
  "Andover":"#d9d9d9",
  "Maidenhead":"#bc80bd",
  "Bracknell":"#ccebc5",
  "Windsor":"#ffed6f"
};

// === MAP INIT ===
const map = L.map('map').setView(MAP_CENTER, MAP_ZOOM);
L.tileLayer('https://{s}.tile.openstreetmap.org/{z}/{x}/{y}.png', { maxZoom: 19, attribution: '© OpenStreetMap contributors' }).addTo(map);
const group = L.layerGroup().addTo(map);

// Draw areas with borders + labels
Object.keys(AREAS).forEach(name => {
  const colour = COLOURS[name] || '#ccc';
  const layer = L.geoJSON(AREAS[name], {
    style: { color:'#222', weight:2, fillColor:colour, fillOpacity:0.5 }
  }).addTo(group);

  try {
    const center = layer.getBounds().getCenter();
    const label = L.divIcon({
      className: 'label',
      html: '<div style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.85); padding:2px 6px; border:1px solid #ccc; border-radius:4px;">'+name+'</div>'
    });
    L.marker(center, {icon: label, interactive:false}).addTo(group);
  } catch(e) {}
});

try {
  const b = group.getBounds();
  if (b.isValid()) map.fitBounds(b.pad(0.2));
} catch(e) {}

// Search + pin
let searchMarker = null;
function dropPin(latlng, label) {
  if (searchMarker) map.removeLayer(searchMarker);
  searchMarker = L.marker(latlng, {
    icon: L.icon({
      iconUrl: 'https://maps.google.com/mapfiles/ms/icons/red-dot.png',
      iconSize: [32,32],
      iconAnchor: [16,32]
    })
  }).addTo(map).bindPopup(label).openPopup();
  map.setView(latlng, 14);
}

// Accept "lat,lon" offline and use Nominatim when online
async function doSearch(q) {
  const m = q.trim().match(/^\s*([+-]?\d+\.?\d*)\s*,\s*([+-]?\d+\.?\d*)\s*$/);
  if (m) {
    const lat = parseFloat(m[1]), lon = parseFloat(m[2]);
    return dropPin([lat,lon], q);
  }
  try {
    const res = await fetch('https://nominatim.openstreetmap.org/search?format=json&q='+encodeURIComponent(q));
    const data = await res.json();
    if (!data || !data.length) return alert('No results found');
    const p = data[0];
    dropPin([parseFloat(p.lat), parseFloat(p.lon)], p.display_name);
  } catch(e) {
    alert('Search failed (offline?). Try lat,lon like 51.331,-0.741');
  }
}

document.getElementById('go').addEventListener('click', () => doSearch(document.getElementById('q').value));
document.getElementById('q').addEventListener('keydown', e => { if (e.key === 'Enter') doSearch(e.target.value); });
</script>
</body>
</html>

Here’s a single-file HTML you can copy into Notepad and save as uk_boundaries_map.html. Then double-click it to open. It uses the same setup as your rehab map (Leaflet + online OSM tiles), and it fetches the 12 boundaries from the MapIt links at runtime. You’ll get: zoom, search with pin, coloured fills, black borders, and the name label centered in each area. Center is Frimley Park Hospital.

If you later want a fully-offline version (with all GeoJSON embedded), I can generate that too once tools are available.

html
<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <title>UK Boundaries Map — Frimley Park</title>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">

  <!-- Leaflet + Geocoder (CDN, same style as your rehab map) -->
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://unpkg.com/leaflet@1.9.4/dist/leaflet.css" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://unpkg.com/leaflet-control-geocoder/dist/Control.Geocoder.css" />
  <style>
    html, body, #map { height: 100%; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
    #toolbar {
      position: absolute; left: 10px; top: 10px; z-index: 1000;
      background: #fff; padding: 10px; border-radius: 8px;
      box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.25);
      display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;
    }
    #q { width: 300px; padding: 6px 8px; }
    .label {
      pointer-events: none;
      font-weight: 700;
      font-size: 14px;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div id="toolbar">
    <input id="q" placeholder="Search a place or lat,lon (e.g. 51.331,-0.741)" />
    <button id="go">Search</button>
  </div>
  <div id="map"></div>

  <!-- JS libs -->
  <script src="https://unpkg.com/leaflet@1.9.4/dist/leaflet.js"></script>
  <script src="https://unpkg.com/leaflet-control-geocoder/dist/Control.Geocoder.js"></script>

  <script>
  // === Map init (Frimley Park Hospital) ===
  const MAP_CENTER = [51.3313, -0.7414];
  const MAP_ZOOM = 11;

  const map = L.map('map').setView(MAP_CENTER, MAP_ZOOM);
  L.tileLayer('https://{s}.tile.openstreetmap.org/{z}/{x}/{y}.png', {
    maxZoom: 19, attribution: '© OpenStreetMap contributors'
  }).addTo(map);

  const group = L.layerGroup().addTo(map);

  // === Area list (name -> MapIt GeoJSON URL) ===
  const AREAS = [
    { name: "Surrey Heath", url: "https://mapit.mysociety.org/area/2450.geojson" },
    { name: "Guildford and Waverley", url: "https://mapit.mysociety.org/area/148924.geojson" },
    { name: "Northwest Surrey", url: "https://mapit.mysociety.org/area/148928.geojson" },
    { name: "Petersfield", url: "https://mapit.mysociety.org/area/143985.geojson" },
    { name: "Bordon", url: "https://mapit.mysociety.org/area/15020.geojson" },
    { name: "Northeast Hampshire", url: "https://mapit.mysociety.org/area/65729.geojson" },
    { name: "Basingstoke", url: "https://mapit.mysociety.org/area/163583.geojson" },
    { name: "Winchester", url: "https://mapit.mysociety.org/area/169780.geojson" },
    { name: "Andover", url: "https://mapit.mysociety.org/area/153770.geojson" },
    { name: "Maidenhead", url: "https://mapit.mysociety.org/area/169633.geojson" },
    { name: "Bracknell", url: "https://mapit.mysociety.org/area/169820.geojson" },
    { name: "Windsor", url: "https://mapit.mysociety.org/area/169781.geojson" }
  ];

  // Stable colour palette (12 distinct)
  const COLOURS = [
    "#8dd3c7","#ffffb3","#bebada","#fb8072",
    "#80b1d3","#fdb462","#b3de69","#fccde5",
    "#d9d9d9","#bc80bd","#ccebc5","#ffed6f"
  ];

  // Load and draw each area
  async function addArea(area, idx) {
    try {
      const res = await fetch(area.url, { headers: { "Accept": "application/json" }});
      if (!res.ok) throw new Error("Fetch failed: " + area.name);
      const gj = await res.json();

      const layer = L.geoJSON(gj, {
        style: {
          color: "#000",
          weight: 2,
          fillColor: COLOURS[idx % COLOURS.length],
          fillOpacity: 0.5
        }
      }).addTo(group);

      // Center label
      try {
        const center = layer.getBounds().getCenter();
        const label = L.divIcon({
          className: 'label',
          html: '<div style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.85); padding:2px 6px; border:1px solid #ccc; border-radius:4px;">'
                + area.name + '</div>'
        });
        L.marker(center, { icon: label, interactive: false }).addTo(group);
      } catch (e) {}

    } catch (err) {
      console.error(err);
      alert("Couldn’t load boundary: " + area.name);
    }
  }

  (async () => {
    for (let i = 0; i < AREAS.length; i++) {
      await addArea(AREAS[i], i);
    }
    // Fit bounds after a short tick so layers are present
    setTimeout(() => {
      try {
        const b = group.getBounds();
        if (b.isValid()) map.fitBounds(b.pad(0.2));
      } catch (e) {}
    }, 400);
  })();

  // === Search + pin (rehab style) ===
  let searchMarker = null;
  function dropPin(latlng, label) {
    if (searchMarker) map.removeLayer(searchMarker);
    searchMarker = L.marker(latlng, {
      icon: L.icon({
        iconUrl: 'https://maps.google.com/mapfiles/ms/icons/red-dot.png',
        iconSize: [32,32],
        iconAnchor: [16,32]
      })
    }).addTo(map).bindPopup(label).openPopup();
    map.setView(latlng, 14);
  }

  async function doSearch(q) {
    const m = q.trim().match(/^\s*([+-]?\d+\.?\d*)\s*,\s*([+-]?\d+\.?\d*)\s*$/);
    if (m) {
      const lat = parseFloat(m[1]), lon = parseFloat(m[2]);
      return dropPin([lat,lon], q);
    }
    try {
      const res = await fetch('https://nominatim.openstreetmap.org/search?format=json&q=' + encodeURIComponent(q));
      const data = await res.json();
      if (!data || !data.length) return alert('No results found');
      const p = data[0];
      dropPin([parseFloat(p.lat), parseFloat(p.lon)], p.display_name);
    } catch (e) {
      alert('Search failed (offline?). Try lat,lon like 51.331,-0.741');
    }
  }

  document.getElementById('go').addEventListener('click', () => doSearch(document.getElementById('q').value));
